sentences: The band was formed in 1999 after ex-Boys Life member Brandon Butler relocated from Kansas to the Washington, D.C. area and briefly fronted the band Farewell Bend.
The band released their first LP in 2001 on John Wall's Slowdime Records and toured nationally afterwards.
The self-titled album was picked up and re-released by Gern Blandsten Records, who also released their second full-length, "Empty Rooms," in 2002.
On November 19, 2010, Canyon reunited as a four-piece featuring Butler, Winkle, and a supporting rhythm section, to play at the Black Cat in Washington DC.
Canyon (Slowdime Records, 2001; re-released on Gern Blandsten Records)
